3 The role ofthe cutoff
Let us now comment on the role of the high wave vector cutoff. Of course, any well-defined elastic theory does involve a coarse-graining cutoff a−1, and the elastic constants κ(a), κ6(a), and κ8(a) depend on it. Thanks to the high-order bending elastic constants κ6 and κ8, there was no need to introduce a cutoff to calculate the interaction between the quadratic pointwise inclusions considered here. This is however somewhat arbitrary, since the microscopic length b arising fromthis procedure is expected to compare with the natural cutoff a. This simply means that reintrocuding the cutoff would merely redefine b, leaving its order of magnitude unchanged. It is, therefore, unimportant to specify whether the cutoff was introduced or not in the procedure defining the microscopic length b that appears in the interaction.
